      "id": "PopularPost239555",
      "post_content": "This card is a ton of fun in EDH. Just today, it stole me a game that I had no business winning.  \n  \nHere's the scenario. I was playing my [Brion Stoutarm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Brion Stoutarm) deck against my friend's [Jaya Ballard](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=109752) deck. He had a [Mana Flare](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mana Flare) on the field and 12 Mountains, and I only had 4 Plains and 4 Mountains. He was at 31 life, and I was at 45 life.   \n  \nDuring his turn, he used about 4 different burn spells (the first of which was a [Past in Flames](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Past in Flames)) to get me down to 17 life. With 6 cards in hand, he passed the turn. I knew that I probably had one turn to live, as his deck is somewhat based around spells with X costs. With no cards in hand, I drew, hoping to pull anything that could help my situation. In what was possibly the luckiest topdeck I've ever had, I drew [Wild Ricochet](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Wild Ricochet). I passed the turn.  \n  \nEyes gleaming, my friend drew, then played a [Banefire](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Banefire) for 22 damage. ... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Lief098",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost239555\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_post\">This card is a ton of fun in EDH. Just today, it stole me a game that I had no business winning.<br/><br/>Here's the scenario. I was playing my <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Brion Stoutarm\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Brion Stoutarm\">Brion Stoutarm</a> deck against my friend's <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardid=\"109752\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=109752\">Jaya Ballard</a> deck. He had a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Mana Flare\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mana Flare\">Mana Flare</a> on the field and 12 Mountains, and I only had 4 Plains and 4 Mountains. He was at 31 life, and I was at 45 life. <br/><br/>During his turn, he used about 4 different burn spells (the first of which was a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Past in Flames\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Past in Flames\">Past in Flames</a>) to get me down to 17 life. With 6 cards in hand, he passed the turn. I knew that I probably had one turn to live, as his deck is somewhat based around spells with X costs. With no cards in hand, I drew, hoping to pull anything that could help my situation. In what was possibly the luckiest topdeck I've ever had, I drew <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Wild Ricochet\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Wild Ricochet\">Wild Ricochet</a>. I passed the turn.<br/><br/>Eyes gleaming, my friend drew, then played a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Banefire\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Banefire\">Banefire</a> for 22 damage. ... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 239555)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postDetails